observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Honorable Mayor agreed to enjoin the department heads to assist the Municipal Accountant in the implementation of COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated                November 25, 2015 for Local Road Network and COA Circular          No. 2016-004 dated September 30, 2016 in the implementation of the accounting system and the new chart of accounts relative to other Public Infrastructure accounts, inviting attention to the following responsibilities:

a. The Municipal Treasurer (i) maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map, (ii) keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components, (iii) render a Report on Local Road Network of the Municipality at the end of the accounting period, and (iv) provide copies of memorandum of agreements, service contracts and other agreements with respect to deposits of funds and other contracts which affect the accounting of financial assets and liabilities and the management of physical assets of the local government unit; and 

b. The Municipality Inventory Team                    (i) conduct an inventory of the local roads under the Municipal Government’s jurisdiction, (ii) prepare the Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System, and (iii) reconcile the list of inventory per local road inventory report and road map with those recorded in the Registry of Public Infrastructure;

c. The Municipal Engineer provide the Municipal Accountant Treasurer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects identified and provide report on the cost and status of   on-going projects and submit detailed cost of components of infrastructure projects;


d. The Municipal Accountant (i) analyze the Registry of Public Infrastructure on Roads and other Public Infrastructure accounts, and identify the accounts to be recorded back in the books of accounts, (ii) prepare the Journal Voucher (JV) to record the beginning balance of the local road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local Road Network Ledger Card respectively,                (iii) support the JV with  Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads, working paper on the distribution of costs for road components, and working paper on the determination of the depreciated replacement cost for the road components with no available cost per registry, (iv) keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network, and (v) prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year; and 


e. The Municipal Budget Officer provide the updated Registries of Appropriation, Allotment and Obligations and furnish copies of the approved budget, supplemental budget, realignment and distribution of the lump sum appropriation and the corresponding legislative approval.

